-- Slovak President to Ask Fico to Form New Cabinet Tomorrow
-- B y   R a d o s l a v   T o m e k
-- 2012-03-14T16:24:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-14/slovak-president-to-ask-fico-to-form-new-cabinet-tomorrow.html
Slovak President Ivan Gasparovic
will tomorrow ask  Robert Fico , whose Smer party won the
elections last week, to form a new Cabinet.  Gasparovic will hand Fico the mandate at about noon in
Bratislava, Slovakia’s capital, presidential press department
said in an e-mailed statement today.  Fico’s Smer may rule without a partner after it garnered 83
of parliament’s 150 seats in the March 10 vote. The party won
the elections on pledges to support poorer citizens while
raising taxes for the top earners and most profitable companies.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Radoslav Tomek in Bratislava at 
 rtomek@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  